                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.5045/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Cape Haitien</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wood</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cape Haitien</hi>
                        </placeName> [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-04">undated</date>].<lb/>[Received
                        December 4, 1929—3:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Demonstration sympathetic with disturbance in Port-au-Prince has developed here,
                    mob numbering about one thousand parading. No violence as yet. May be necessary
                    to declare martial law.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wood</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
